def: A childish play, in which one covers his eyes, and guesses whostrikes him or his hand placed behind him.
The branch of science which treats of fossil footprints.

On a painting, and sometimes in a bas-relief, mosaic picture,or the like, that part of the scene represented, which is nearest tothe spectator, and therefore occupies the lowest part of the work ofart itself. Cf. Distance, n., 6.
A suffix composed of -able and the adverbial suffix -ly; as,favorably.
A searcher; an explorer; an investigator. [Obs.]Searched into by such skillful indagators of nature. Boyle.
Capable of being misinterpreted; liable to be misunderstood.
